Task #18 follow-up: redesign Windows OOP applier (PowerShell, no staged/)

Field bug report: cmd window flashed visible, parent never exited, payload
in .ota-pending never extracted on Windows. The Task #18 OOP applier was
unfit for the field.

Root causes:
1. cmd.exe + windowsHide is unreliable when spawned detached on Win10/11.
2. cmd's `tasklist /FI "PID eq X" | find` parent-wait loop can hang
   forever on PID reuse.
3. app.exit(0) was being called from updater.init(), which main.js wires
   in BEFORE app.whenReady() — pre-ready app.exit doesn't actually
   terminate the parent, so the asar lock never releases.

Redesign (mirrored in walok/electron/updater.js and walok/server/electron/updater.js):
- Replaced cmd.exe + apply.cmd with powershell.exe + apply.ps1.
  Args bound through PowerShell param() (no shell injection surface).
  -WindowStyle Hidden reliably hides the console.
- Eliminated the staged/ subfolder. Expand-Archive extracts payload.zip
  directly onto the install dir (the user's "delete everything, just
  extract" model — implemented via -Force overwrite, NOT pre-wipe, so
  user data files outside the payload survive).
- Pre-write three overlay files at .ota-pending root from Node:
  cleanup-marker.json, current-exe-sidecar.json, merged-ota-config.json
  (version-bumped clone preserving customer fields). PowerShell copies
  them into the install dir post-extract.
- Parent-wait uses Get-Process -Id $pid + StartTime comparison captured
  at script start to defeat PID reuse.
- Replaced app.exit hook with process.exit (hard kill) so the parent
  actually terminates regardless of whenReady state.
- Added SUCCESS-marker sweep at the top of applyPendingUpdateOnStartup:
  if a prior OOP run wrote SUCCESS but its background self-cleanup
  didn't reach the pending dir before the NEW exe boots, wipe the
  pending dir and move on (no re-apply loop).

Test coverage:
- test-rebrand-update.js: rewrote 3 OOP scenarios for new contract,
  added SUCCESS-sweep scenario. 116 assertions (was 111).
- test-server-rebrand.js: added server SUCCESS-sweep + hard-kill exit
  hook regression tests. 65 assertions (was 58).
- test-build-all-logo-isolation.js: 39 assertions, unchanged.
- All 220 assertions pass.

Architect code review fed back two real issues, both fixed:
1. Server updater still used app.exit fallback in OOP exit hook — now
